Subject: [PATCH] riscv64 Rust-core bun: stub TinyCC externs on riscv64 (link fix)

config.ts disables TinyCC for riscv64 (`cfg.tinycc = !(... || riscv64)`), so
libtcc.a is not built/linked. But two Rust sites declare the `tcc_*` externs
gated on `not(any(android, freebsd, windows-aarch64))` — a list that OMITS
riscv64 — so on riscv64 the real `extern "C"` block is emitted and the symbols
are referenced (via the FFI compile path reachable from JS bindings), failing
the final link:

    ld.lld: error: undefined symbol: tcc_new / tcc_compile_string / tcc_relocate / ...

Both sites carry a comment to "keep this predicate in sync with `cfg.tinycc`";
0001 added riscv64 to cfg.tinycc but missed these. Add `target_arch = "riscv64"`
to both the `not(any(...))` (real externs) and the `any(...)` (unreachable!()
stub definitions) so riscv64 links against the stubs. The runtime ENABLE_TINYCC
early-returns in bun_runtime::ffi keep callers off the stubs, and the
`unreachable!()` makes any future gate regression loud.

diff --git a/src/runtime/ffi/mod.rs b/src/runtime/ffi/mod.rs
index 940a6a56..c6dde965 100644
--- a/src/runtime/ffi/mod.rs
+++ b/src/runtime/ffi/mod.rs
@@ -123,7 +123,8 @@ mod TCC {
     #[cfg(not(any(
         target_os = "android",
         target_os = "freebsd",
-        all(windows, target_arch = "aarch64")
+        all(windows, target_arch = "aarch64"),
+        target_arch = "riscv64"
     )))]
     unsafe extern "C" {
         pub(super) fn tcc_delete(s: *mut State);
@@ -131,7 +132,8 @@ mod TCC {
     #[cfg(any(
         target_os = "android",
         target_os = "freebsd",
-        all(windows, target_arch = "aarch64")
+        all(windows, target_arch = "aarch64"),
+        target_arch = "riscv64"
     ))]
     pub(super) unsafe fn tcc_delete(_s: *mut State) {
         unreachable!("tcc_delete: TinyCC not built on this target (cfg.tinycc = false)");
